Fig. 6(c) shows a comparison between the XRD patterns of five just-milled compositions in this solid solution with different Ti4+/Zr4+ ratio (increasing from top to bottom). As mentioned before, the whole pattern shifts towards low angles as the Zr content increases. Samples were also analyzed by scanning electron microscopy finding out that they consist basically of sub-micron size agglomerates of irregular shape (Fig. 7
). Chemical composition was analyzed by EDS revealing atomic ratios very close to those of the nominal compositions. The two-zirconate end members, Y2Zr2O7 and Gd2Zr2O7
, were found to present the highest specific surface area (12.3 and 9.1m2/g, respectively) of all the analyzed samples with the remaining compositions giving values within the 5–7.5m2/g range. A study of the electric properties of these samples [13], have shown similar values to those obtained by other more complex processing methods.
